&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;'''Saposa-Tinputz'''<br>
|}

The family of '''Saposa-Tinputz languages''' is a subgroup of the [[Nehan-North Bougainville Solomonic languages]]. It consists of four [[language]]s.  They are largely spoken on the island of [[Bougainville Island|Bougainville]] in [[Papua New Guinea]].

==Components==

*[[Hahon language|Hahon]]
*[[Saposa language|Saposa]]
*[[Teop language|Teop]]
*[[Tinputz language|Tinputz]]

